# Cursor rules ŌĆö OKF Weaver

`AGENTS.md` (and `docs/spec.md`) are the source of truth for how this repo
works; read them first. This file mirrors the load-bearing rules so Cursor has
them inline. When code and spec disagree, treat `docs/spec.md` as authoritative
and update it alongside the code.

## What this is

A stateless web app that ingests a relational database schema (raw SQL DDL from
any RDBMS, or a dbt `manifest.json`), uses Claude to generate curated Open
Knowledge Format (OKF) context per table, validates it, lets a human review and
edit, and exports a portable OKF bundle. No accounts, no persistence, no live
database connectors in v1.

## Architecture

Two independently deployed services: `frontend/` (Next.js, Vercel) is a thin
client; `backend/` (FastAPI + Pydantic + Anthropic, Render) does all parsing,
LLM calls, validation, and serialization so the API key and prompt logic stay
server-side. Pipeline: `ingest/` -> `SchemaIR` -> `ai/` (Claude tool use,
streamed over SSE) -> `okf/validate.py` -> `okf/serialize.py`.

## Load-bearing decisions (do not silently change)

- **Pydantic v2 is the single source of truth for every shape** ŌĆö `SchemaIR`,
  `OKFBundle`/`OKFTable`/`OKFColumn`, AI tool output, and all API bodies are the
  same reused models. Structural OKF validity *is* successful `OKFBundle`
  construction; cross-field rules are `@model_validator` methods. Model output
  and human edits pass through the identical gate.
- **Model is `claude-sonnet-4-6` with adaptive thinking** (Opus 4.6 as the
  quality upgrade). 4.6 surface: no `budget_tokens`, no assistant prefill.
- **Constrained output via tool use, not native structured outputs** ŌĆö one
  `emit_okf_table` tool whose schema is `OKFTable.model_json_schema()`; parse
  the tool call with `OKFTable.model_validate(...)`.
- **OKF v0.1**, pinned in one constant (`OKF_SPEC_VERSION`).
- **1 table per model call by default** (finest streaming, no cross-table
  contamination, cheap via prompt caching).
- **Trust guardrails:** never auto-publish without human approval; the model
  self-reports per-field confidence and low-confidence fields are flagged; the
  system prompt forbids inventing columns/tables and prefers existing dbt
  descriptions.
- **Deployment is via platform git integration, not CI** ŌĆö Vercel + Render
  auto-deploy on push to `main`. GitHub Actions is tests-on-PR only; do not add
  deploy steps to it.

## Conventions

- TDD (red-green-refactor); one test file per module
  (`okf/validate.py` -> `tests/test_okf_validate.py`); mock the Anthropic call
  in unit tests, keep any live call behind a mark.
- Backend uses `uv` ŌĆö never bare `pip` or `uv pip`. Commit `uv.lock`.
- Keep modules under ~500-600 lines. Never hardcode secrets; `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`
  is server-side only.
